2) Evaluation using common-knowledge attributes: Because my only stated preference is a general enjoyment of CDs, I relied on features that typically make a compilation CD broadly enjoyable on physical disc — concise, well-produced tracks, strong vocal performances, and a varied but accessible track list that rewards repeated listening. Ladies & Gentlemen: The Best of George Michael is a career-spanning greatest-hits compilation containing many well-known, tightly produced pop and soul songs (for example, widely recognized singles such as "Careless Whisper," "Faith," and "Freedom! '90"). Those songs are typically short-to-medium in length, vocally focused, and mastered for mainstream release, which tends to make for immediate, gratifying CD listening sessions. Turn It On Again: The Hits (Genesis) is also a legitimate hits compilation, but Genesis’s catalog spans progressive rock textures and longer, more instrumentally complex arrangements alongside later pop hits; some material reflects extended instrumental sections and progressive tendencies that can be more specialized in appeal.
