Net assessment: The dance‑pop disc satisfies the core, repeatedly stated elements of my preference set — syncopated bass emphasis, punchy percussion, layered yet glossed production, strong midrange/punch and dynamics — whereas With the Beatles, though coherent and warm, leans into jangly guitar and early‑60s pop textures that run counter to my stated dislike of guitar‑forward mixes and low‑end‑deficient early‑60s pop. That makes the dance‑pop title the better fit.

